    <div class="small-12 large-12 columns">
      <%= image_tag 'hotel.jpg', class: 'big_day_photo-left', align: 'left'%>
      <p>
        <h2>Hotel</h2>
      </p>
      <p>
        <% if [:asmita_family, :asmita_family_friend].include?(current_user.group_name) %>
          For those that have filled out the RSVP, hotel rooms at the Marriott Downtown will be provided for the number of nights requested and a booking confirmation will be sent to the login e-mail. 
        <% else %>
          We have reserved a block of rooms at the Marriott Downtown which can be booked through the following <a href="https://resweb.passkey.com/Resweb.do?mode=welcome_ei_new&eventID=14462273" target="_blank">link.</a>
        <% end %>
      </p>
      <h3>Hotel Parking</h3>
      <p>     
        Valet Parking is available at the hotel for $60 per day. Alternatively, parking is available at a cheaper rate at two lots on Albany Street. This <a href="http://nyc.bestparking.com/neighborhoods/financial-district-parking" target="_blank">site</a> provides a guide to parking in the area.
      </p>
      <h3>Transportation from Major Airports</h3>
      <p>     
        For those arriving from airports, the Marriott Downtown is accessible in the following <a href="http://www.marriott.com/hotels/maps/travel/nycws-new-york-marriott-downtown/" target="_blank">ways</a>. We have included some tips from our own experience. 
      </p>
      <h4>Newark Liberty Airport (EWR)</h4>
      <p>
        <span class="bold">Uber (Convienient)</span> - The estimated fare for UberX is $41-$47.
      </p>
      <p>
        <span class="bold">Public Transport (Economical)</span> -  The fare is $4.25 per person + $1 for a new metrocard. Take Bus 62 to Newark Penn Station. The fare is $1.50 per person and the bus offers no change. Follow the signs for the Path and purchase a Metrocard (yellow). Take the Path Train to World Trade Center. One way fare is $2.75. After exiting, World Trade Center walk to the hotel provided walking directions are available.
      </p>
      <h4>LaGuardia Airport (LGA)</h4>
      <p>
        <span class="bold">Uber (Convienient)</span> - The estimated fare for UberX is $37-$49. 
      </p>
      <p>
        <span class="bold">Public Transport (Economical)</span> -  The fare is $2.75 per person + $1 for a new metrocard. Take bus Q70 from La Guardia to 74 St/Roosevelt Subway Stop, connect to the E train and get off at the World Trade Center stop. Walk 8 min to the hotel provided walking directions are available. More routes are available <a href="http://web.mta.info/nyct/service/airport.htm" target="_blank">here but this has the best signage.</a>
      </p>
      <h4>John F. Kennedy Airport (JFK)</h4>
      <p>
        <span class="bold">Taxi (Convienient)</span> - There is a flat fare of $52 before tolls, tax, and gratuity. Read more  <a href="http://www.panynj.gov/airports/jfk-taxi-car-van-service.html" target="_blank">here</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <span class="bold">Public Transport (Economical)</span> -  The fare is $7.75 per person + $1 for a new metrocard. Follow signs for the AirTrain from your terminal and board a Howard Beach bound AirTrain. Exit the AirTrain at Howard Beach, purchase a metrocard with at least $7.75 fare, and connect to the NYC subway. Take the A train to Manhattan and exit at the Chambers Street stop. Walk 8 minutes to the hotel provided walking directions are available. This is a very straightforward and well signed route up to Chambers Street.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
