<div class="section">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="small-12 large-12 columns">
      <%= image_tag 'skyline.jpg', class: 'big_day_photo-left', align: 'left'%>
      <p>
        <h2>Things to Do in NYC</h2>
      </p>
      <p>
        If you are looking for additional things to do, <a href="http://www.tripadvisor.com/Attractions-g60763-Activities-New_York_City_New_York.html" target="_blank">Trip Advisor</a> is a good resource. Additionally, here are our thoughts on New York’s attractions.
      </p>
      <% if [:asmita_family, :asmita_family_friend].include?(current_user.group_name) %>
      <p>
        If you’re joining us for the bus or boat tour, we’ll take you past most of New York’s iconic attractions. The boat will get pretty close to the Statue of Liberty which in our opinion is enough to view it.
      </p>
      <% end %>
      <h3>Art Museums</h3>
      <p>
        Some art museums are pay what you wish and others have free days. Check this <a href="http://www.nyc-arts.org/collections/35/free-museum-days-or-pay-what-you-wish" target="_blank">link</a> to see if any of the musuems you are interested in have any policies.
      </p>
      <h3>Intrepid Museum</h3>
      <p>
        One of Eric’s favorite muesums in the city. The <a href="http://www.intrepidmuseum.org/" target="_blank">museum</a> is located on an aircraft carrier and has exhibits featuring military planes and the Enterprise space shuttle. Buy tickets online beforehand to avoid long queues. 
      </p>
      <h3>Scenic Vistas</h3>
      <p>
        The Empire State Building, Top of the Rock, and One World Trade Center all offer great views of the New York skyline. If you visit one, you’ve visited all three in many New Yorker’s opinions.  
      </p>
      <h3>Favorite Free Attractions</h3>
      <p>
        Walk on the Highline, Walk in Central Park, and Walk around Times Square at night.
      </p>
      <h3>Favorite Neighborhoods</h3>
      <p>
        East, West, and Greenwich Village
      </p>
      <h3>Attractions Near the Hotel</h3>
      <p>
        One World Observatory, Memorial Pools, Wall St, the Bull, Battery Park, Statue of Liberty, South Street Seaport,  The Brooklyn Bridge.
      </p>
      <h3>Broadway</h3>
      <p>
        For those unfamiliar with Broadway, we recommend Wicked or Aladdin. For those who’ve seen quite a few shows, checkout this <a href="http://broadwayforbrokepeople.com/" target="_blank">website</a> for a list of shows and how to get cheaper tickets.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
